] at the [[University of Pennsylvania]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bioethics.upenn.edu/People/?last=Fiester&first=Autumn|title=The Department of Medical Ethics & Health Policy, Perelman School of Medicine at the University of Pennsylvania \u2013 Department of Medical Ethics & Health Policy|publisher=}}</ref>\n* Margot Rogers (1986), Chief of Staff to [[United States Secretary of Education]] [[Arne Duncan]]\n* Michael W. Welch (1986), Director, National Association of Air Traffic Specialists, Mayor,North Pole,Alaska, State Deputy 2009-2012 Alaska Knights of Columbus <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.naatsalaska.net |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-06-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080609083253/http://www.naatsalaska.net/ |archivedate=2008-06-09 }};</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.northpolealaska.com|title=Home Page|publisher=}}</ref>\n* [[Mark Lemley]] (1986), Professor of Law, Stanford Law School\n* [[Michelle Alexander]] (1987), Associate Professor, Ohio State University, civil rights advocate and writer\n* Maryam Banikarim (1987), Chief Marketing Officer at [[Univision]]<ref>[http://www.univision.net/corp/en/pr/New_York_13062005-2.html Press Release: Univision Names Maryam Banikarim Chief Marketing Officer<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n* [[Neil Gorsuch]] (1987), Associate Justice of the [[Supreme Court of the United States]]\n* Christopher W. Kersey (1989), Founding Managing Partner of Havencrest Healthcare Capital Partners and Chairman of the Board of Johns Hopkins Medicine International\n* [[Brad Lander]] (1989), Member of the [[New York City Council]], representing the 39th Council District in Brooklyn\n* Catherine Sheehan (1989), Deputy Assistant Inspector General at the [[United States Department of Justice|Department of Justice]] <ref>[http://www.usdoj.gov/oig/offices/ovr_txt.htm DOJ/OIG Organization \u2013 Oversight and Review Division Text Version<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070313160708/http://www.usdoj.gov/oig/offices/ovr_txt.htm |date=2007-03-13 }}</ref>\n* [[George Herbert Walker IV]] (1989), CEO of [[Neuberger Berman]]\n* [[Jason Saul]] (1989), CEO of Mission Measurement, Lecturer of Social Enterprise at [[Kellogg School of Management]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kellogg.northwestern.edu/faculty/directory/saul_jason.aspx|title=Jason Saul \u2013 Faculty \u2013 Kellogg School of Management|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n=== 1990s ===\n* [[Noah Feldman]] (1990), Professor of Law, Harvard Law School\n* [[Mark Sandy]] (1991), Deputy Associate Director for National Security, Office of Management and Budget, Executive office of the President, Washington, D.C.\n* Amy Hungerford (1992), Professor and Director of Undergraduate Studies of English at Yale University\n* [[Rich Constable]] (1993), former assistant U.S. attorney, Commissioner of the N.J. Department of Community Affairs\n* Maj. John Carr (1993), former [[United States Air Force]] prosecutor at the [[Guantanamo Bay detainment camp]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mindfully.org/Reform/2005/Guantanamo-Prosecutors-Quit1aug05.htm|title=Two Prosecutors At Guantanamo Quit in Protest: Rather than take part in military trials they considered rigged against alleged terrorists held at Guantanamo Bay, Cuba  JESS BRAVIN / Wall Street Journal 1aug2005|last=mindfully.org|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061005233013/http://www.mindfully.org/Reform/2005/Guantanamo-Prosecutors-Quit1aug05.htm|archivedate=2006-10-05}}</ref>\n* Rodney Martin (1993), CEO, Native American Policy & Law Expert, former Commissioner on the [[Arizona]] Commission of Indian Affairs, Former Judge Judge, Ex Congressional Staff to Congressman Ed Pastor (D-AZ), former amateur Middleweight Boxer.\n* [[Rachel Paulose]] (1993), [[United States Attorney]] for [[Minnesota]]\n* [[Stacey Abrams]] (1994), [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] [[Georgia House of Representatives|House Minority Leader]], 84th Dis